// A device's `#foreign` externs are its IMPLEMENTATION, private to the device (they sit behind net's
// `#module` band). They are NOT part of net's public API: an importer can reach neither the qualified
// `net.net_listen` (not in net's export set) NOR the bare `net_listen` — the visibility gate rejects a
// bare reference that binds only to another unit's non-exported decl. Only net's arche wrappers
// (net.listen/connect/send/recv/close) are public. The raw C symbol stays LINKABLE at the ABI level
// (unavoidable), but arche name resolution no longer reaches it across the device boundary. This pins
// that a device's raw implementation does not leak past its contract — visibility is enforced for a
// `#foreign` extern exactly as for a pure-Arche `#module` decl.
// RUN: %arche check %s > %t.out 2>&1 ; grep -qi "Undefined symbol 'net_listen'" %t.out
#import { net }
entry :: system {
  net_listen(8081)(s:); // raw extern is private to `net` — not visible here
}

#run entry
